OL,3,C'He gave me a job and a room and took
OL,4,Cmy money'
OL,6,FThrough a strong support network of
OL,7,Fexperts, modern slavery survivors are
OL,8,Fhelped to rebuild their lives,
OL,9,Fphysically and emotionally.
OL,11,F"Sometimes you see people who are very
OL,12,Fbroken, very lost when they first come
OL,13,Fto us," Mr Hilton said. "And then they
OL,14,Fstart to grow and develop and become
OL,15,Fthemselves. Learning to be themselves
OL,16,Fagain. And that's really important.
OL,17,FWhen you've lost everything just to
OL,18,Fget some ID, for instance, is huge for
OL,19,Fthem... because that's been robbed of
OL,20,Fthem. Their identity has been taken."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/11
